L,'emails',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(852,1,'2015-05-08 17:17:20','2015-05-12 17:19:10',1,'de',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'de',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Angie Keefer \r\n‘Area Variance’\r\nEröffnung Dienstag 3. März 2015, 19:00 Uhr\r\n\r\nVom 3. März bis zum 12. April 2015 präsentiert der Kunstverein München im Schaufenster am Hofgarten ‘Area Variance’– eine Ausstellung von Angie Keefer.\r\n\r\nIm Zentrum der Ausstellung ‘Area Variance’ von Angie Keefer stehen zwei heruntergekommene Fassaden in Hudson, New York. Im Rahmen eines öffentlichen Kunstprojekts 2014 ließ die Künstlerin die Fassaden mit einem Metallic-Autolack besprühen, durch den sie in eine einzelne golden schimmernde, monochrome Skulptur verwandelt wurden. Anschließend wurde sie fotografiert, das Foto auf Metallicpapier gedruckt und aufwendig gerahmt in mehreren großen Finanzzentren in Europa ausgestellt.\r\n\r\nDer Marktwert dieser gerahmten Fotografie schwankt dabei mit dem Wert jener Immobilien, die es zeigt: 248 und 250 Columbia Street.\r\n\r\nEin Künstlergespräch mit Angie Keefer findet am Samstag, den 14. März 2015 um 19:00 Uhr im Foyer des Kunstvereins München statt.\r\n\r\n[+]\r\n\r\nEröffnung am Freitag 24. April 2015, 19:00 Uhr\r\n\r\nAnne-Mie Van Kerckhoven \r\n‚Serving Compressed Energy with Vacuum’\r\n\r\n25. April bis 14. Juni 2015\r\n\r\n[+]\r\n\r\nGiovanni Oberti ‚Onorarono’ im Schaufenster am Hofgarten\r\n\r\n25. April bis 17. Mai 2015\r\n\r\n[++]\r\nAngie Keefer\r\n‘Area Variance’\r\nOpening Tuesday 3 March 2015, 7.00pm\r\n\r\nFrom 3 March until 12 April 2015, Kunstverein München presents ‘Area Variance’—an exhibition by Angie Keefer in the Hofgarten Window.\r\n\r\nAngie Keefer’s ‘Area Variance’ entails a pair of dilapidated façades in Hudson, New York. For a public art commission in 2014, the artist arranged for the façades to be sprayed with metallic auto-body paint—transforming them into a single, shimmering, golden, monochromatic sculpture, which was subsequently registered as a photograph, printed on metallic paper, and elaborately framed for exhibition in major financial centers throughout Europe.\r\n\r\nThe commercial value of the framed photograph will fluctuate with the real estate value of the properties it depicts: 248 and 250 Columbia Street.\r\n\r\nAngie Keefer will deliver a talk in the Foyer of the Kunstverein on Saturday 14 March 2015 at 7.00pm.\r\n\r\n[+]\r\n\r\nOpening Friday 24 April 2015, 7.00pm\r\n\r\nAnne-Mie Van Kerckhoven \r\n\'Serving Compressed Energy with Vacuum’\r\n\r\n25 April to 14 June 2015\r\n\r\n[+]\r\n \r\nGiovanni Oberti \'Onorarono’ in Schaufenster am Hofgarten\r\n\r\n25 April to 17 May 2015 ','Kunstverein München\r\nGaleriestrasse 4\r\n[++]\r\nt+ 49 89 221 152\r\nf+ 49 89 229 352'),(853,1,'2015-05-08 17:44:54','2015-05-08 17:44:54',NULL,'2015-05-08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(854,1,'2015-05-08 17:51:14','2015-05-08 20:19:11',2,'en',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'en',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Angie Keefer, ‘Area Variance’\r\nOpening Tuesday 3 March 2015, 7.00pm','From 3 March until 12 April 2015, Kunstverein München presents ‘Area Variance’—an exhibition by Angie Keefer in the Hofgarten Window.\r\n\r\nAngie Keefer’s ‘Area Variance’ entails a pair of dilapidated façades in Hudson, New York. For a public art commission in 2014, the artist arranged for the façades to be sprayed with metallic auto-body paint—transforming them into a single, shimmering, golden, monochromatic sculpture, which was subsequently registered as a photograph, printed on metallic paper, and elaborately framed for exhibition in major financial centers throughout Europe.\r\n\r\nThe commercial value of the framed photograph will fluctuate with the real estate value of the properties it depicts: 248 and 250 Columbia Street.\r\n\r\nAngie Keefer will deliver a talk in the Foyer of the Kunstverein on Saturday 14 March 2015 at 7.00pm.','Kunstverein München\r\nGaleriestraße 4\r\n80539 München\r\nt +49 89 221 152\r\nf +49 89 229 352\r\nwww.kunstverein-muenchen.de'),(856,1,'2015-05-12 11:28:21','2015-11-26 16:29:38',NULL,'2015-05-11 Screening and talk with Stephan Dillemuth ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-11-screening-and-talk-with-stephan-dillemuth',NULL,'2015-05-11 19:00:00','2015-05-11 19:00:00',NULL,NULL,'','Monday 11 May 2015\r\n7.00pm\r\n\r\nScreening and talk with Stephan Dillemuth\r\n\r\nStephan Dillemuth will talk through and contextualize rarely-seen video documentation of several shows organized at Friesenwall 120, an artist-run space he co-ran with Merlin Carpenter, Josef Strau, and Nils Norman in Cologne in the early Nineties. The screening includes footage of ‘Internationale Situationniste’ and \'Wahrheit ist Arbeit – wie es wirklich war’ from 1992 – the latter of which was an unofficial restaging of \'Wahrheit ist Arbeit\', originally a three-person exhibition by Werner Büttner, Martin Kippenberger and Albert Oehlen at Museum Folkwang from 1984. Before the show at Friesenwall 120, former Kunstverein München director Helmut Draxler attempted to remount \'Wahrheit ist Arbeit’ in 1992, which ultimately resulted in a different show by the same three artists retitled \'Mahlen ist Wahlen\'.\r\n\r\nOrganised by Kunstverein München’s curator Saim Demircan as part of the teaching block ‘Countercultural Curating’ – a series of lectures designed for students from the Akademie der Bildenden Künste München, and related public events throughout May, June and July together with artists Stephan Dillemuth, Dan Mitchell, John Russell, and Head Gallery.\r\n',''),(857,1,'2015-05-12 11:49:43','2015-06-29 14:57:05',NULL,'<u>Impressions of Youth in an Epoch of Death: The Beginnings and Ends of Vetjylien N\'gyrz</u>  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'uimpressions-of-youth-in-an-epoch-of-death-the-beginnings-and-ends-of-vetjylien-ngyrzu',NULL,'2014-09-24 00:00:00','2014-11-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'','<u>Impressions of Youth in an Epoch of Death: The Beginnings and Ends of Vetjylien N\'gyrz</u>  \r\n\r\n24 September to 2 November 2014\r\nIn the window display of Kunstverein München \r\n\r\nArtist’s Veit Laurent Kurz and Julien Nguyen have created a special window display dedicated to their fictitious character, the crypto-polymath Vetjylien N’gyrz.\r\n\r\nThe first iteration of N’gyrz was the basis for the exhibition ‘Flowers of Paranoia’ in Frankfurt earlier this year, where the character - an ongoing collaborative project by Kurz and Nguyen - was introduced as an enduring influence for the apocryphal occult-band Servants Order ov Ancient Psychik Youth (S.O.A.P.Y). Following this, the artists use Kunstverein München’s window display as an appendix to their false historicisation of N’gyrz in the literary vein of mythoposeia – a genre of expansive mythology to works of fiction\r\n\r\nAn aged rock wall is installed as the backdrop for materials relating to the character’s early life as a botanist on the cusp of a formative moment that leads him to perverse thought and experimentation. Fashioned in the style of a grotto or early Christian catacomb, the display is infused with rusty tech, scepters and a veneration icon of a young N\'gyrz.',''),(859,1,'2015-05-13 10:32:34','2015-11-26 16:29:49',NULL,'2015-05-12 Walking tour of <u>Serving Compressed Energy with Vacuum</u>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-12-walking-tour-of-userving-compressed-energy-with-vacuumu',NULL,'2015-05-12 19:00:00','2015-05-12 20:00:00',NULL,NULL,'','Tuesday 12 May 2015\r\n7pm\r\n\r\nWalking tour of Anne-Mie Van Kerckhoven\'s exhibition, \'Serving Compressed Energy with Vacuum\'\r\n\r\nChris Fitzpatrick, director of Kunstverein München, will walk through the exhibition, discussing how the 40-year survey was conceived, as well as how the publication and public programming extend its scope, and why Van Kerckhoven\'s artistic practice remains a hard-wired necessity, not a profession.',''),(858,1,'2015-05-12 20:21:45','2015-05-13 16:31:35',NULL,'2015-05-12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(860,1,'2015-05-15 13:18:43','2015-09-16 16:37:50',NULL,'Thomas Locher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'thomas-locher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Thomas Locher, <u>Präambel und Grundrechte im Grundgesetze für die Bundesrepublik Deutschland Artikel 1 - 19 [Diskurs2] Ein Kommentar</u>\r\n\r\n13. Juli bis 10. September 1995',''),(861,1,'2015-05-15 13:27:27','2015-06-24 17:42:53',NULL,'Thomas Locher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'thomas-locher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<u>Thomas Locher\r\nPräambel und Grundrechte im Grundgesetze für die Bundesrepublik Deutschland Artikel 1 - 19 [Diskurs2] Ein Kommentar</u>\r\n\r\nDeutschland, 1995\r\nDeutsch, und Englisch\r\n116 Seiten\r\nVerlegt von Kunstverein München e.V.\r\nISBN 3-923357-10-9\r\n\r\nHerausgegeben von Hedwig Saxenhuber, und Thomas Locher\r\n\r\nTexte von Thomas Locher, und Christoph Menke\r\n\r\nDesign Kühle & Moser, und Thomas Locher',''),(862,1,'2015-05-15 13:32:10','2015-06-24 17:43:32',NULL,'Thomas Locher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'thomas-locher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<u>Thomas Locher\r\nPreamble and basic rights in the basic law of the republic of Germany [Discourse2] A Commentary</u>\r\n\r\nGermany, 1995\r\nEnglish, and German\r\n116 pages\r\nPublished by Kunstverein München e.V.\r\nISBN 3-923357-10-9\r\n\r\nEdited by Hedwig Saxenhuber, and Thomas Locher\r\n\r\nText by Thomas Locher, and Christoph Menke\r\n\r\nDesigned by Kühle & Moser, and Thomas Locher',''),(863,1,'2015-05-15 13:33:13','2015-05-15 13:39:28',NULL,'Thomas Locher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'thomas-locher',NULL,'1995-12-12 00:00:00','1995-12-12 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'','Thomas Locher, \'Preamble and basic rights in the basic law of the republic of Germany [Discourse2