 Street.',''),(1422,1,'2016-01-12 14:25:49','2016-01-12 14:43:50',98,'2002',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2002',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(1423,1,'2016-01-12 14:26:44','2016-01-12 16:47:12',NULL,'Christine Borland',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'christine-borland',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Christine Borland\r\n*Inside Pocket*, in the \'shop windows\' of Kunstverein München, as part of an ongoing retrospective exhibition of the artist\'s work.\r\n13 July 2002 until 1 September, 2002\r\n\r\nCurated by Maria Lind\r\n\r\nSince April 2002 we have presented works by Christine Borland (Glasgow) in a survey exhibition. The pieces were shown one at a time over a period of a year, in different locations within Kunstverein München and in other public space. Over the last few months the works: *The Dead Teach the Living*, Small Objects that Save Lives*, *Inside Pocket*, Shows with .10mm Hole*, *From Life*, and *Berlin Blanket* have been shown. The seventh station *HeLa Hot* was exhibited in the lobby of the Kunstverein until 2 May 2003. The eighth and final station, *A Place Where Nothing Has Happened* will be shown in the grounds of the Academy of Fine Arts (Akademie der Bildenden Künste) in Munich.\r\n\r\n\r\n\'...when I was directing Kunstverein München we did a retrospective with Christine Borland for the duration of a year, in which only one work was shown at a time, and this was intimately connected to how her work operates. It is dense, it requires a lot of time to make and then to engage with, and it also deals with the passage of time.\' —Maria Lind, <a href=\'http://moussemagazine.it/articolo.mm?id=759\'>Mousse Magazine</a>',''),(1424,1,'2016-01-12 14:27:26','2016-01-12 14:44:01',86,'2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(1425,1,'2015-05-12 11:49:43','2015-06-29 14:57:05',NULL,'<u>Impressions of Youth in an Epoch of Death: The Beginnings and Ends of Vetjylien N\'gyrz</u>  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'uimpressions-of-youth-in-an-epoch-of-death-the-beginnings-and-ends-of-vetjylien-ngyrzu',NULL,'2014-09-24 00:00:00','2014-11-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'','<u>Impressions of Youth in an Epoch of Death: The Beginnings and Ends of Vetjylien N\'gyrz</u>  \r\n\r\n24 September to 2 November 2014\r\nIn the window display of Kunstverein München \r\n\r\nArtist’s Veit Laurent Kurz and Julien Nguyen have created a special window display dedicated to their fictitious character, the crypto-polymath Vetjylien N’gyrz.\r\n\r\nThe first iteration of N’gyrz was the basis for the exhibition ‘Flowers of Paranoia’ in Frankfurt earlier this year, where the character - an ongoing collaborative project by Kurz and Nguyen - was introduced as an enduring influence for the apocryphal occult-band Servants Order ov Ancient Psychik Youth (S.O.A.P.Y). Following this, the artists use Kunstverein München’s window display as an appendix to their false historicisation of N’gyrz in the literary vein of mythoposeia – a genre of expansive mythology to works of fiction\r\n\r\nAn aged rock wall is installed as the backdrop for materials relating to the character’s early life as a botanist on the cusp of a formative moment that leads him to perverse thought and experimentation. Fashioned in the style of a grotto or early Christian catacomb, the display is infused with rusty tech, scepters and a veneration icon of a young N\'gyrz.',''),(1426,1,'2016-01-12 14:39:34','2016-01-12 14:43:12',88,'2012',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2012',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',''),(1427,1,'2016-01-12 14:41:37','2016-01-12 15:45:50',NULL,'The Local Contemporary',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'the-local-contemporary',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Over the course of 2012, the series *The Local Contemporary* will present four young positions of the art and design field within the new Kunstverein München Display Window. These positions address a sense of locality, from the specific site of the Hofgarten to the city of Munich. By using this space, the Kunstverein intends to show the creative potential amongst local networks that operate in its hometown alongside its international program.\r\n\r\nKunstverein München Display Window (Project Space) is supported by Kulturstiftung der Stadtsparkasse München.\r\n\r\nCurated by Anja Lückenkemper',''),(1428,1,'2016-01-12 14:42:45','2016-01-12 15:07:30',NULL,'<u>Tischlein Deck Dich</u>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'utischlein-deck-dichu',NULL,'2012-12-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Stefan Hoffmann, Thomas Wolf, and Norman Herwig\r\n*Tischlein Deck Dich*\r\n2 December, 2012 until 6 January, 2013\r\n\r\n(as part of the series, *The Local Contemporary*)\r\n\r\nCurated by Anja Lückenkemper',''),(1429,1,'2016-01-12 14:54:13','2016-01-12 15:08:30',NULL,'<u>Ayzit Bostan</u>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'uayzit-bostanu',NULL,'2012-07-14 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Ayzit Bostan\r\n*Landwehrstraße*\r\n14 July until 9 September, 2012\r\n\r\n(as part of the series, *The Local Contemporary*)\r\n\r\nCurated by Anja Lückenkemper',''),(1430,1,'2016-01-12 14:57:03','2016-01-12 15:08:10',NULL,'<u>Heike Jobst</u>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'uheike-jobstu',NULL,'2012-04-28 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Heike Jobst\r\n*Folly Gardens*\r\n28 April until 17 June, 2012\r\n\r\n(as part of the series, *The Local Contemporary*)\r\n\r\nCurated by Anja Lückenkemper',''),(1431,1,'2016-01-12 15:02:53','2016-01-13 11:02:59',NULL,'<u>My Bauhaus is Better Than Yours</u>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'umy-bauhaus-is-better-than-yoursu',NULL,'2012-02-18 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<u>My Bauhaus is Better Than Yours</u>\r\n18 February until 15 April, 2012\r\n\r\nA selection of k.m publications from 1970 until today. \r\n\r\n(as part of the series, *The Local Contemporary*)\r\n\r\nCurated by Anja Lückenkemper\r\n\r\n<a href=\'http://betterbau